       <li class="widget-container widget_text" id="text-3">
        <h3 class="widget-title">
         PJHC in the News
        </h3>
        <div class="textwidget">
         <p>
          • Wiki Education recently published an article by
          <strong>
           Katie Webber ’19
          </strong>
          on
          <a href="https://wikiedu.org/blog/2017/05/23/how-editing-wikipedia-empowers-students-a-reflection/">
           her experiences contributing to Wikipedia
          </a>
          as part of HUMA/SOCI 371: Poverty, Justice, and Human Capabilities. Katie’s entirely new article on the Montrose Center was featured in the “Did You Know” section on Wikipedia’s main page this spring.
          <br/>
          • PJHC minor
          <strong>
           Anna Thomas ’18
          </strong>
          shared
          <a href="http://pjhc.rice.edu/pjhc-in-the-news/%22http://news.rice.edu/2016/09/19/uncovering-history/">
           her experiences
          </a>
          from her summer at the Rice Archaeological Field School in Tanzania.
          <br/>
          •
          <strong>
           Bridget Schilling ’17
          </strong>
          received the
          <a href="http://cswgs.rice.edu/schilling/">
           2017 Merfish Award
          </a>
          in recognition of her sustained commitment and leadership in advancing social justice, gender equality and inclusivity on campus, in Houston, and beyond.
         </p>
         <p>
          For more stories about PJHC students and faculty, click
          <a href="http://pjhc.rice.edu/pjhc-in-the-news/">
           here
          </a>
          .
         </p>
        </div>
       </li>
      </ul>
